      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "Assessing use of knowledge by policy-makers may require strategies such as interviews and analysis of documents (e.g., reviewing policies to assess use of evidence). When assessing use of knowledge by physicians, we could measure use of paths of care or ordering of relevant medications, which are often measured through use of administrative or clinical databases."
